<node id="Compiler">
  <data key="d0">Compiler</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Compiler is a program in computer science that translates, transforms, or converts a high-level programming language program into a functionally equivalent low-level programming language program, such as assembly language or machine language. It serves as a type of translator, taking human-readable source code and generating target code that computers can execute directly. This process enables programs written in high-level languages to run on computer hardware, as computers natively understand only low-level instructions.

Unlike an interpreter, which reads and executes source code statements directly, a compiler produces target code (such as machine instructions) to be executed later. The act of compilation involves efficient and equivalent translation, ensuring that the resulting low-level program faithfully reflects the logic and behavior of the original high-level program.

In educational contexts, the compiler is often illustrated or described in contrast to interpreters. One illustrative depiction describes a person in formal attire holding a green board or paper, symbolizing the translation process—conceptually processing source text (for example, in English) and outputting the equivalent program in another language (such as Chinese). Overall, a compiler forms a critical component in software development, bridging the gap between human intent expressed in high-level code and executable instructions understood by computer hardware.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-524488f325e3b749520b26154058ac49&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aa6a6137fde10652cd93a8bcf9ffebcf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-896812268ddab3f8ba43e409ef31f0f6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb64dc11aeecd21521a2af6a8cfa8093&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ecf31faebdcc696eee3f0300603ac136&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8151fd6721162afb5261395661b1280c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed7293e9aeec5ea94f7f86f4ae119370&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e5b7ce5bd1723067a738bbe62a548e6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-769c2785e5eaa135d71c12ae137012bd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e4e6dd16b5efe88951506ef1089b4714&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2693f7eed941d7a575fb48103191b9f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-be01738fa65ffd9fde1205d015283524&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2a29dd8f170730feb43137deb71f6861&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6737524161da7d35b4f23f14c5047487&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-58f59c2e670bb8779699efd00a5d0689&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-006cd400ede79791d562a634055a0181&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9ab812108c1d67da8cf205eff9b21211&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-939c20c7d9cbf4dcc11abf5ae47b2975&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b141de5784e7c358ae42229b3b2f7482&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d3f98c0ae34a8f4f3f8c11b867518860&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c9ca390783bdb296cb9297d2e99a9290&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b502762bbfbf1513c1ccaa956b9f21f6</data>
