</node>
<node id="Target Program">
  <data key="d0">Target Program</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">A target program is a program generated in the target language by a translator or compiler, functionally equivalent to the source program.&lt;SEP&gt;Target Program is an output that is typically generated by compilers but is not produced in the interpreter process as described in the slide.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-524488f325e3b749520b26154058ac49&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d08d8e4136ef0aa05f56218c9bf547a</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781618659</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="High-Level Programming Language">
  <data key="d0">High-Level Programming Language</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">High-level programming language is a programming language with abstraction from machine details, analyzed as the source language by compilers.&lt;SEP&gt;High-level programming language refers to the source programming language that is transformed by a compiler into a lower-level form.&lt;SEP&gt;High-Level Programming Language refers to abstract source code languages designed for humans to write software, such as the programs converted by a compiler.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-524488f325e3b749520b26154058ac49&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8151fd6721162afb5261395661b1280c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9ab812108c1d67da8cf205eff9b21211</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781618631</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Low-Level Programming Language">
  <data key="d0">Low-Level Programming Language</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Low-level programming language is a language closer to machine code, such as assembly language or machine language, used as the target language by compilers.&lt;SEP&gt;Low-Level Programming Language is the target of the compilation process, typically assembly or machine code.&lt;SEP&gt;Low-level programming language denotes the target language produced after compilation, such as assembly or machine code.&lt;SEP&gt;Low-Level Programming Language refers to programming languages closer to machine code, including assembly and machine language, which are the output of a compilation process.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-524488f325e3b749520b26154058ac49&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb64dc11aeecd21521a2af6a8cfa8093&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8151fd6721162afb5261395661b1280c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9ab812108c1d67da8cf205eff9b21211</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781618628</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Assembly Language">
  <data key="d0">Assembly Language</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Assembly language is a type of low-level programming language often used as a target language by compilers.&lt;SEP&gt;Assembly language is a type of low-level programming language that is one of the possible outputs of a compiler.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-524488f325e3b749520b26154058ac49&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-006cd400ede79791d562a634055a0181</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
