<node id="Host Machine">
  <data key="d0">Host Machine</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">A host machine is the computer that runs the compiler during the compilation process.&lt;SEP&gt;A host machine is the computer on which the compiler is run.&lt;SEP&gt;Host machine refers to the machine where the compilation process occurs.&lt;SEP&gt;Host Machine is the computing platform where the compiler operates and performs the compilation.&lt;SEP&gt;Host machine is the computer on which the compiler runs and converts the source code during the compilation process.&lt;SEP&gt;Host Machine is the system on which a cross compiler is run and compiles code.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-524488f325e3b749520b26154058ac49&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-769c2785e5eaa135d71c12ae137012bd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2693f7eed941d7a575fb48103191b9f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-be01738fa65ffd9fde1205d015283524&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2a29dd8f170730feb43137deb71f6861&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6737524161da7d35b4f23f14c5047487</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781618634</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Target Machine">
  <data key="d0">Target Machine</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">A target machine is the computer that runs the resulting target language program.&lt;SEP&gt;A target machine is the computer architecture for which the compiled code is generated.&lt;SEP&gt;Target machine is the machine for which the compiler generates code, and where the resulting low-level program is intended to run.&lt;SEP&gt;Target Machine is the computing platform for which the machine language program is generated during the compilation process.&lt;SEP&gt;Target machine is the computer for which the machine code is generated and on which the program is run.&lt;SEP&gt;Target Machine is the system for which a cross compiler generates machine code.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-524488f325e3b749520b26154058ac49&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-769c2785e5eaa135d71c12ae137012bd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2693f7eed941d7a575fb48103191b9f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-be01738fa65ffd9fde1205d015283524&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2a29dd8f170730feb43137deb71f6861&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6737524161da7d35b4f23f14c5047487</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781618635</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cross Compiler">
  <data key="d0">Cross Compiler</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Cross Compiler is a type of compiler that generates machine or executable code for a target platform different from the one on which the compiler itself is executed. Specifically, a cross compiler operates on a host machine and is designed to produce code that will run on a distinct target platform, meaning the architecture or operating environment for which the resulting code is intended differs from where the compilation process takes place.

This distinction is fundamental in software development scenarios where the target platform is either not powerful or convenient enough to support native compilation, or where code must be prepared for multiple platforms from a single development environment. Cross compilers thus play a crucial role in embedded systems development, portability of software projects, and situations involving heterogeneous computing environments.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-524488f325e3b749520b26154058ac49&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-769c2785e5eaa135d71c12ae137012bd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e4e6dd16b5efe88951506ef1089b4714&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2693f7eed941d7a575fb48103191b9f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-be01738fa65ffd9fde1205d015283524&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2a29dd8f170730feb43137deb71f6861&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6737524161da7d35b4f23f14c5047487&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-58f59c2e670bb8779699efd00a5d0689&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-006cd400ede79791d562a634055a0181&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9ab812108c1d67da8cf205eff9b21211&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-939c20c7d9cbf4dcc11abf5ae47b2975&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b141de5784e7c358ae42229b3b2f7482</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781618637</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Retargetable Compiler">
  <data key="d0">Retargetable Compiler</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A retargetable compiler is a compiler in which only machine-dependent components need modification to generate code for different target platforms.&lt;SEP&gt;Retargetable Compiler is a compiler designed to be easily adapted for output to multiple target machine architectures.&lt;SEP&gt;A retargetable compiler is a compiler structured such that only the machine-dependent part needs to be changed to support different hardware platforms.&lt;SEP&gt;Retargetable Compiler is a type of compiler designed to be easily adapted to generate code for different machine architectures.&lt;SEP&gt;A retargetable compiler is capable of being adapted or configured to generate code for multiple target machine architectures.&lt;SEP&gt;A retargetable compiler is a compiler architecture designed to be easily adaptable to generate code for multiple target platforms.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-524488f325e3b749520b26154058ac49&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-58f59c2e670bb8779699efd00a5d0689&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-006cd400ede79791d562a634055a0181&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9ab812108c1d67da8cf205eff9b21211&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-939c20c7d9cbf4dcc11abf5ae47b2975&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b141de5784e7c358ae42229b3b2f7482</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781618642</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
