</node>
<node id="High-Level Language Program">
  <data key="d0">High-Level Language Program</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">High-Level Language Program refers to source code written in a high-level programming language that is designed for human readability and abstraction from the underlying machine hardware. Unlike low-level languages, such as assembly or machine code, a high-level language program employs syntax and constructs that are closer to natural human language, making it user-friendly and easier for programmers to write, understand, and maintain.

This entity serves as the initial input to the compilation process, where the source code—often depicted as a box labeled '高级语言程序' or as a blue rectangle in flow diagrams—is provided to a compiler. The purpose of the compiler is to translate the high-level language program into a lower-level, machine-executable form. High-level language programs are distinguished by their abstraction from the hardware details, offering greater convenience and modularity for software development.

Overall, a high-level language program encapsulates the original, human-readable source code written in advanced programming languages. This code represents the primary material for translation into machine-understandable instructions, facilitating efficient software engineering and program execution.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-aa6a6137fde10652cd93a8bcf9ffebcf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-896812268ddab3f8ba43e409ef31f0f6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb64dc11aeecd21521a2af6a8cfa8093&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ecf31faebdcc696eee3f0300603ac136&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8151fd6721162afb5261395661b1280c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed7293e9aeec5ea94f7f86f4ae119370&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e5b7ce5bd1723067a738bbe62a548e6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-769c2785e5eaa135d71c12ae137012bd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e4e6dd16b5efe88951506ef1089b4714&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2693f7eed941d7a575fb48103191b9f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-be01738fa65ffd9fde1205d015283524&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2a29dd8f170730feb43137deb71f6861&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6737524161da7d35b4f23f14c5047487&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-58f59c2e670bb8779699efd00a5d0689&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-006cd400ede79791d562a634055a0181&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9ab812108c1d67da8cf205eff9b21211&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-939c20c7d9cbf4dcc11abf5ae47b2975&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b141de5784e7c358ae42229b3b2f7482</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781618621</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Low-Level Language Program">
  <data key="d0">Low-Level Language Program</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Low-Level Language Program refers to computer code that is written in or transformed into assembly language or machine language, which are types of languages that are closely related to the fundamental instructions recognized by computer hardware. This code is typically generated as the output of the compilation process, where a higher-level programming language is translated by a compiler into a form that the machine can directly execute.

These programs are characterized by their proximity to the underlying hardware, allowing direct control and efficient execution but often at the cost of human readability and portability. Assembly and machine code, the primary forms of low-level language programs, allow instructions to be executed directly by the computer. Low-level language programs thus serve as an essential bridge between human-readable source code and device-level operations, enabling high-level software to function on physical hardware.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-aa6a6137fde10652cd93a8bcf9ffebcf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-896812268ddab3f8ba43e409ef31f0f6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ecf31faebdcc696eee3f0300603ac136&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed7293e9aeec5ea94f7f86f4ae119370&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e5b7ce5bd1723067a738bbe62a548e6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-769c2785e5eaa135d71c12ae137012bd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e4e6dd16b5efe88951506ef1089b4714&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2693f7eed941d7a575fb48103191b9f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2a29dd8f170730feb43137deb71f6861&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-58f59c2e670bb8779699efd00a5d0689&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-006cd400ede79791d562a634055a0181&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b141de5784e7c358ae42229b3b2f7482</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781618620</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Execution">
  <data key="d0">Execution</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Execution refers to the process in which the low-level language program is run to produce results.&lt;SEP&gt;Execution refers to running the machine language program to yield a result.&lt;SEP&gt;Execution is the act of running a machine language program to produce the result.&lt;SEP&gt;Execution is the process in which the resulting machine language program is run to produce the final result.&lt;SEP&gt;Execution is the process where a machine language program is run to produce a result.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-aa6a6137fde10652cd93a8bcf9ffebcf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-896812268ddab3f8ba43e409ef31f0f6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ecf31faebdcc696eee3f0300603ac136&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-be01738fa65ffd9fde1205d015283524&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-58f59c2e670bb8779699efd00a5d0689</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781618617</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Results">
  <data key="d0">Results</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Results are the output produced after the execution of the low-level language program.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-aa6a6137fde10652cd93a8bcf9ffebcf</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781618617</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Lecturer">
  <data key="d0">Lecturer</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The entity "Lecturer" refers to the individual delivering the instructional content in the context of recorded or streaming educational videos, specifically pertaining to subjects such as compiler theory and programming language processing. Across various depictions, the Lecturer consistently appears as a male-presenting individual, typically wearing a brown or tan suit with a collared or white shirt, and is positioned either behind a podium, lectern, or desk.

The Lecturer is shown either in the main video frame or as an inset, sometimes presented on the right side or embedded as a photo overlay within the slide. A defining feature is the intentional blurring of the Lecturer’s facial features to ensure privacy compliance, making the individual's identity unrevealed. The scenes frequently include a blue-toned or digital world map as a backdrop, indicating a studio or professional setting.

Throughout the presentations, the Lecturer is engaged in actively delivering content—gesturing to explain slide material, presenting synchronous instructional or educational explanations, and providing context directly related to topics such as compilation, interpretation, and programming languages. This consistent portrayal marks the Lecturer as the principal instructor or presenter facilitating learning within MOOCs and other online video-learning environments.</data>
