<node id="NUDT">
  <data key="d0">NUDT</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">NUDT, which stands for the National University of Defense Technology, is referenced prominently throughout the described educational video material. The acronym "NUDT" appears repeatedly as part of the digital background, often superimposed on a stylized world map or a blue map motif behind the lecturer. This branding includes both the organization’s logo and name, and is consistently featured in various forms, such as watermarks, textual labels, or faint inscriptions in the backdrop of the lecture slides and video frames.

The recurrent presence of NUDT’s branding elements—acronym, logo, and name—strongly indicates institutional affiliation with the educational content being presented. As an academic institution, NUDT is likely responsible for either organizing, sponsoring, or directly delivering the lecture, as suggested by its central role in the visual context. The referenced environment is characterized as both technological and educational, reflecting NUDT’s identity as a university specializing in defense technology.

The context of the references underscores NUDT’s formal status as an academic organization, with its branding serving to authenticate and contextualize the lecture within the university’s domain. This suggests that the National University of Defense Technology is either the host or principal institution associated with the course or instructional material showcased in the video, reinforcing its prominence and relevance in relation to the presented educational content.</data>
