<node id="Assembly Language Program">
  <data key="d0">Assembly Language Program</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">An assembly language program is a type of low-level language program output by a compiler, typically used as an intermediate step before machine language.&lt;SEP&gt;An assembly language program is written in assembly language and is a type of low-level language used as output from a compiler.&lt;SEP&gt;An assembly language program is a form of low-level language mentioned as a possible output from the compilation process, serving as an intermediary between high-level language and machine language.&lt;SEP&gt;Assembly language program is another example of low-level language program, written in a programming language that closely corresponds to machine code.&lt;SEP&gt;An assembly language program is a type of low-level code that can be produced by a compiler.&lt;SEP&gt;Assembly Language Program is a low-level program that can result from compilation, used as an example in the explanation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-aa6a6137fde10652cd93a8bcf9ffebcf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ecf31faebdcc696eee3f0300603ac136&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed7293e9aeec5ea94f7f86f4ae119370&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e5b7ce5bd1723067a738bbe62a548e6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-769c2785e5eaa135d71c12ae137012bd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-be01738fa65ffd9fde1205d015283524</data>
  <data key="d4">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d5">1781618623</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Machine Language Program">
  <data key="d0">Machine Language Program</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A Machine Language Program is the most fundamental type of computer program, consisting of instructions expressed in the native binary language that a computer's central processing unit (CPU) can directly understand and execute. It is a specific kind of low-level program, where the code comprises sequences of binary instructions tailored to the architecture of the target machine.

Typically, a Machine Language Program is produced as the final output by a compiler that translates higher-level programming languages into machine-readable form. This code—which is sometimes depicted in flowchart diagrams labeled as '机器语言程序'—serves as the fully translated executable representation intended for direct execution by computer hardware.

Due to its nature, a Machine Language Program is the most basic and direct way of programming a computer, bypassing any need for interpretation or translation at runtime. Every instruction within a Machine Language Program corresponds exactly to operations supported by the hardware, making it the ultimate low-level program executed by the CPU. This direct execution capability distinguishes it from higher-level or interpreted programming languages, ensuring the fastest and most efficient performance possible by utilizing the computer’s hardware as closely as possible.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-aa6a6137fde10652cd93a8bcf9ffebcf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-896812268ddab3f8ba43e409ef31f0f6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb64dc11aeecd21521a2af6a8cfa8093&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ecf31faebdcc696eee3f0300603ac136&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8151fd6721162afb5261395661b1280c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed7293e9aeec5ea94f7f86f4ae119370&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e5b7ce5bd1723067a738bbe62a548e6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-769c2785e5eaa135d71c12ae137012bd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e4e6dd16b5efe88951506ef1089b4714&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2693f7eed941d7a575fb48103191b9f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-be01738fa65ffd9fde1205d015283524&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2a29dd8f170730feb43137deb71f6861&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6737524161da7d35b4f23f14c5047487&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-58f59c2e670bb8779699efd00a5d0689&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-006cd400ede79791d562a634055a0181&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9ab812108c1d67da8cf205eff9b21211&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-939c20c7d9cbf4dcc11abf5ae47b2975&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b141de5784e7c358ae42229b3b2f7482</data>
