<node id="Interpret And Execute Simultaneously">
  <data key="d0">Interpret And Execute Simultaneously</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Interpret And Execute Simultaneously is a process where the interpreter reads, interprets, and executes the source code line by line in real time.&lt;SEP&gt;Interpret And Execute Simultaneously is the process by which an interpreter directly reads and executes source code line by line rather than producing a compiled target program.&lt;SEP&gt;Interpret And Execute Simultaneously describes the process by which interpreters both interpret and execute each instruction of the source program as it is read, without separately compiling the entire code.&lt;SEP&gt;Interpret And Execute Simultaneously is a key feature of interpreters, representing the idea of translating and executing program code at the same time.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d3f98c0ae34a8f4f3f8c11b867518860&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9868a82502f630570f76085c32ca9c42&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-581187ec0bef8a2764aaa3dfc31d025f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8333ee0b29cc3d6c26d7600e3bfc8036</data>
