  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Compiler" target="Cross Compiler">
  <data key="d7">8.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relation "(Compiler, Cross Compiler)" describes the classification of a cross compiler within the broader category of compilers.

A cross compiler is a specific and specialized type of compiler program that is capable of generating code for a different machine architecture or target platform than the one on which it is running. Unlike standard compilers that produce executable programs for the same architecture as the host machine, a cross compiler targets different platforms for its output, enabling software development and deployment across multiple hardware systems. Cross compilers are commonly listed as a distinct category of compiler in educational materials, such as lecture slides, highlighting their role in enabling code portability and development for systems that may not natively support local compilation.

Overall, the relation underscores that a cross compiler is classified as a type of compiler distinguished by its ability to produce code for architectures or platforms different from the build environment.</data>
  <data key="d9">category,classification,compiler categorization,specialization,subtype,type,type categorization,variant type</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-524488f325e3b749520b26154058ac49&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-769c2785e5eaa135d71c12ae137012bd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2693f7eed941d7a575fb48103191b9f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-be01738fa65ffd9fde1205d015283524&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-58f59c2e670bb8779699efd00a5d0689&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-006cd400ede79791d562a634055a0181&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9ab812108c1d67da8cf205eff9b21211&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-939c20c7d9cbf4dcc11abf5ae47b2975</data>
  <data key="d11">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
  <data key="d12">1781618856</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Compiler" target="Retargetable Compiler">
  <data key="d7">5.0</data>
  <data key="d8">A retargetable compiler is a specialized kind of compiler.&lt;SEP&gt;Retargetable Compiler is a type of compiler program.&lt;SEP&gt;A retargetable compiler is a compiler structured to facilitate easy adaptation for different hardware platforms.&lt;SEP&gt;Retargetable Compiler is a type of compiler that can be adapted for various targets.&lt;SEP&gt;A retargetable compiler is a specialized type of compiler.</data>
  <data key="d9">category,compiler categorization,specialization,subtype,type,variant type</data>
