<edge source="Compiler" target="Machine Language Program">
  <data key="d7">9.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relation "(Compiler, Machine Language Program)" refers to the fundamental process whereby a compiler takes a high-level language program as input and produces a machine language program as output. This process, known as compilation, involves translating or converting source code written in a programming language understandable by humans into a machine language program that can be directly executed by a computer’s hardware.

Throughout the compilation process, the compiler systematically analyzes the high-level language program and, through a sequence of translation steps, generates the corresponding machine language program. This output, also referred to as the target executable, is the direct result of the compiler’s translation process. The primary role of the compiler in this context is thus to bridge the gap between human-oriented programming languages and the low-level instructions required for machine execution.</data>
  <data key="d9">code output,code translation,compilation process,generation,output,output generation,transformation,translation</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-cb64dc11aeecd21521a2af6a8cfa8093&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8151fd6721162afb5261395661b1280c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed7293e9aeec5ea94f7f86f4ae119370&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2693f7eed941d7a575fb48103191b9f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-be01738fa65ffd9fde1205d015283524&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6737524161da7d35b4f23f14c5047487&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9ab812108c1d67da8cf205eff9b21211&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-939c20c7d9cbf4dcc11abf5ae47b2975&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b141de5784e7c358ae42229b3b2f7482</data>
  <data key="d11">1.1.1 什么是编译程序.mp4</data>
