<edge source="Target Machine" target="Cross Compiler">
  <data key="d7">4.0</data>
  <data key="d8">A cross compiler generates machine code for the target machine, which differs from the host machine.&lt;SEP&gt;A cross compiler generates executable code for a target machine that differs from the host machine.&lt;SEP&gt;The cross compiler produces code intended for execution on a target machine different from the host.&lt;SEP&gt;Cross Compiler generates code that will run on the target machine.</data>
  <data key="d9">code deployment,code generation,distinction,output,platform difference,target platform</data>
