<edge source="Low-Level Language Program" target="Assembly Language Program">
  <data key="d7">5.0</data>
  <data key="d8">An assembly language program is a specific type of low-level language program produced during or after compilation.&lt;SEP&gt;Assembly language program is a type of low-level language program discussed in the compiler definition.&lt;SEP&gt;An assembly language program is cited as an example of a low-level language program.&lt;SEP&gt;Assembly language program is another example of a low-level language program.&lt;SEP&gt;An assembly language program is a specific type of low-level language program.</data>
  <data key="d9">category inclusion,classification,example,output form,program type,subtype,type</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-aa6a6137fde10652cd93a8bcf9ffebcf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ecf31faebdcc696eee3f0300603ac136&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed7293e9aeec5ea94f7f86f4ae119370&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e5b7ce5bd1723067a738bbe62a548e6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-769c2785e5eaa135d71c12ae137012bd</data>
