<edge source="Lecturer" target="NUDT">
  <data key="d7">10.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relation "(Lecturer, NUDT)" refers to the association between a lecturer and the institution NUDT, which stands for the National University of Defense Technology. Across multiple descriptions, the lecturer is consistently depicted in a presentation or lecture setting, where several visual cues unequivocally indicate their affiliation with NUDT.

Specifically, the lecturer is observed standing at a podium or in front of a background prominently displaying the acronym "NUDT". In many instances, this backdrop takes the form of a blue, digital world map, further emphasizing the academic or technological context of the presentation and aligning with the institutional branding of the National University of Defense Technology. The presence of the "NUDT" name on the backdrop serves either as a watermark in the video or as faint but recognizable text, solidifying the lecturer's institutional connection.

There is a recurring theme of the lecturer's association being inferred from the visual setting—such as the world map background labeled "NUDT" or the podium placement—rather than from explicit verbal statements or text. While in some cases, it is suggested that the affiliation is implied by visual branding (e.g., watermark, backdrop text), other descriptions interpret this as a direct institutional association, indicating that the lecturer is either representing, affiliated with, or presenting at NUDT.

Overall, the relation "(Lecturer, NUDT)" consistently signifies that the lecturer is associated with the National University of Defense Technology, as demonstrated by the institutional branding present in the lecture or presentation environment.</data>
